<br>
If you are hurt because another class gets picked over you, id think you need to find a new game.<br>
<br>
My characters used to get passed up because of certain things all the time.  Id play my necro and get denied groupage because they needed a tank, or how about my druid getting passed up because they needed a &quot;real&quot; nuker like a wizard.<br>
<br>
This is a game, people take certain classes because thats what they want and or need.  If you believe that your class should be invited to a group over any other class all the time,  you are wrong.   Even if the other class gets invited because you lack one spell or skill that it has.<br>
<br>
Quoting someone off of a board, in one isolated instance, proves absolutely nothing.<br>
<br>
In the end it sucks, it isnt ever fun to have someone else picked over you for a group.  Its like the poor kid who was last to be picked for the team.  Thats the way life is, there always has to be someone picked last or not included.  Its not the same persone every time, especially in EQ.  It all depends on curcumstances.  You just have to suck it up and move on, if you let something like that get you down you'll have a hard time dealing with LIFE!<br>
<br>
