No no, you misunderstand what i meant. Im not upset that i wasnt chosen. If they had picked a wizard, a rogue, or even a monk instead of me, i wouldnt be happy of course but i wouldnt have thought anything was unfair/unbalanced. Those are all damage dealing classes.<br>
<br>
I am upset when people start to get lfg enchanters with cod before they do mages and other damage dealers. Enchanters are not and should not be a better choice for damage dealing than a mage, ever. When they are, its obvious there is no reason to play a damage dealer and no reason not to play an enchanter. End of discussion.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
My characters used to get passed up because of certain things all the time. Id play my necro and get denied groupage because they needed a tank, or how about my druid getting passed up because they needed a &quot;real&quot; nuker like a wizard.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Again, this goes back to my point i was trying to make. A necro isnt going to get chosen over a warrior or sk for a tank, nor should he be. A necro isnt going to get chosen over a wizard or druid for a nuker, because those classes are supposed to do that better.<br>
<br>
However, if someone chooses a mage over a necro for say, dotting, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>there is a problem</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. Do you see my point? Mages are supposed to be one of, if not the most damaging class in the game yet a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>non offensive</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> class like an enchanter can do multiple times the damage of a mage. No one who knows what they are doing would ever pick a mage over a knowledgable enchanter for damage, and no one <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>does</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. <br>
<br>
This makes my game play unenjoyable. This <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>is</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> my problem. <br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
This is a game, people take certain classes because thats what they want and or need. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Somethings wrong when you &quot;want or need&quot; an enchanter before any other class for every role except healer.<br>
<br>
