<br>
They have the best mana regen buffs for other, the best crowd control spells, the best haste spells, and are the second best slowers in the game. You add in CoD pets they are the best damage dealing class in the game.<br>
<br>
How as a Magician am I going to compete with that. I already have to compete with rogues, monks, rangers and wizards for the dps group slots and all have their ups and downs and they cant compete with what an enchanter brings to the table above and beyond dps with the exception of maybe a monk for their pulling skills.<br>
<br>
You enchanters thinking that we are just envious your wrong, I think a lot of Magicians are down right pissed off about it. Magicians have nothing going for us besides dps, we have no needed group buffs, we have no form of damage mitigation, we have no form of crowd control, hell we even had our ability to transfer mana nerfed to near uselessness. On top of all that before when we were unhappy about our situation people would say then go solo but guess what PoP has pretty much made us SoL in that department as well. <br>
<br>
Before you all start trying to defend something like CoD take a close look at the class your defending it against and maybe you could understand why magicians are unhappy. <br>
<br>
When one class is incredibly good at multiple roles that is overpowering. Jeez you are a class that groups seek out without CoD quite often dont you see that, while other classes that have no choice but to be lfg have to sit for at times is hours before they get invited to a group and here you all are being one of the best grouping classes in the game also becoming one of the best soloing classes in the game. <br>
<br>
